LOTTERY REMINDER: Due to the first confirmed case in Wilson, NC of the Coronavirus (COVID-19), the lottery tomorrow will now be modified to the public. Therefore, the only individuals allowed will be a law enforcement officer, board member and several school staff to conduct the lottery. Lottery results will be posted in five business days, which will be Monday, March 23, 2020 by 5:00 p.m.

Please note for the Sibling lottery, if you don't receive a lottery number, your child will be admitted for that selected grade level. If you do receive a sibling lottery number, this means your child will be placed into the lottery that is being held tomorrow due to limited space for that particular grade level.

Thank you in advance for your understanding and consideration! #TigerPride

post_text: It's official! Yesterday, May 25, 2019, the Class of 2019 became the first graduating class at Wilson Preparatory Academy! We also had a 100% graduation rate! We are so proud of these scholars! Their future is bright. They are ready to show the world their Tiger Pride! Here are some pictures from the first graduation ceremony in WPA's history!
text: It's official! Yesterday, May 25, 2019, the Class of 2019 became the first graduating class at Wilson Preparatory Academy! We also had a 100% graduation rate! We are so proud of these scholars! Their future is bright. They are ready to show the world their Tiger Pride! Here are some pictures from the first graduation ceremony in WPA's history!

post_text: We had the dress rehearsal for the first ever graduation at Wilson Preparatory Academy today. We also had our first ever Senior Picnic! Oh, did we mention that the world famous Ed Mitchell from Mitchell's Barbecue and "The Pit" catered the Senior Picnic? Exciting times at WPA!

post_text: Today was the last day of school at Wilson Preparatory Academy. We always close out our year with an assembly with our scholars to announce our Co-Teachers of the Year. This year, it was a tie! Watch the scholars reaction when we announced that Ms. Stephanie Sanders and Mr. Stephen Howell were our 2019 Teachers of the Year! They were excited!

post_text: Our first graduating class at Wilson Preparatory Academy wore their caps and gowns for the first time at school today. The K-11th grade scholars were excited to see the Class of 2019 in their caps and gowns! Our Seniors are onlys days away from graduation! #tigerpride
